arXiv:2601.14646v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We study iterated weighted residual (WR) splittings generated by a positive operator $R_{0}\in B\left(Hight)_{+}$ and a finite family of contractions $C_{1},\dots,C_{m}$ in $B\left(Hight)$. The associated residual update $R\mapsto R^{1/2}(I-C^{*}_{j}C_{j})R^{1/2}$ produces an $m$-ary energy tree of residuals $\left\{ R_{w}ight\} $ and dissipated pieces $\left\{ D_{w,j}ight\} $ indexed by finite words. From this tree we construct intrinsic path measures on the path space by biasing transitions either by a fixed quadratic form $x\mapsto\left\langle x,D_{w,j}xightangle $ (defining the measures $
u_{x}$) or, in the trace-class setting, by ${m tr}\left(D_{w,j}ight)$ (yielding a reference measure $
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$). When $R_{0}\in S_{1}\left(Hight)_{+}$, we show that $
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$ dominates the family $\left\{ 
u_{x}ight\} $ and identify $d
u_{x}/d
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$ as a canonical martingale limit of cylinder likelihood ratios. Along $
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$-almost every branch the residuals decrease to a terminal trace-class random variable $R_{\infty}$, which we interpret as the WR boundary variable. We then disintegrate $
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$ over $\sigma\left(R_{\infty}ight)$, obtaining a boundary law $\mu_{\mathrm{tr}}=\left(R_{\infty}ight)_{\#}
u_{\mathrm{tr}}$ and conditional path measures $\left\{ 
u^{T}_{\mathrm{tr}}ight\} $. Finally, we show that each $
u_{x}$ admits a boundary representation as a mixture of $\left\{ 
u^{T}_{\mathrm{tr}}ight\} $ with an explicit boundary density $h_{x}=d\mu_{x}/d\mu_{\mathrm{tr}}$, thereby organizing the family of intrinsic WR path measures by a single trace-biased boundary disintegration.
